article.headline: Northern Iowa 71, Illinois St. 66
article.story: CEDAR FALLS, Iowa (AP) -- Grant Stout scored 19 points and Eric Coleman added 15 to lead Northern Iowa past Illinois State 71-66 Saturday. Jared Josten added 13 for the Panthers (18-12, 9-9 MVC), who won their second straight after a 1-9 skid that likely ruined their at-large NCAA tournament hopes. Boo Richardson brought Illinois State (15-15, 6-12) within 63-61 on a 3-pointer with 2:02 left, and Levi Dyer cut the Panthers' lead to one on a 3 with 50 seconds left. Brooks McKowen answered with two free throws for Northern Iowa. Dyer missed a three on the other end that would have tied the game, and Josten grabbed the rebound and hit two from the line to seal the victory. Dyer led Illinois State with 17 points. Richardson added 14.
